tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE SwimmerPerformanceTracking (
    swimmer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    swimmer_name VARCHAR(50),
    swimmer_age INT,
    swimmer_gender VARCHAR(10),
    swimmer_team VARCHAR(50),
    swim_event VARCHAR(50),
    swim_time DECIMAL(5,2)
);

CREATE TABLE Performances (
    PerformanceID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    SwimmerID INT,
    Event VARCHAR(255),
    Time VARCHAR(10),
    FOREIGN KEY (SwimmerID) REFERENCES Swimmers(ID)
);

CREATE TABLE Swimmers (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(50),
  age INTEGER,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  date_of_birth DATE
);

CREATE TABLE SwimTimes (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  swimmer_id INTEGER REFERENCES Swimmers(id),
  event VARCHAR(50),
  time INTEGER,
  date_recorded TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE SwimCompetitions (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  competition_name VARCHAR(100),
  location VARCHAR(100),
  date TIMESTAMP,
  winning_swimmer_id INTEGER REFERENCES Swimmers(id)
);

CREATE TABLE Results (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    swimmer_id INT,
    competition_id INT,
    event_id INT,
    time DECIMAL(5,2),
    FOREIGN KEY (swimmer_id) REFERENCES Swimmers(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (competition_id) REFERENCES Competitions(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES Events(id)
);
